  "texts": [
    "Many scholars have proposed counterfactual approaches that received scholars' attention, such as performance improvement for multi-agent learning, causal inference in machine learning, explanation for system decision of black-box models, the actionable alternative outcome of existing and new AI models, etc.",
    "[70,[137][138][139][140][141][142].",
    "Academics are exploring trade-offs to generate counterfactual explanations and methods to utilize the generated CFs to provide explainable and interpretable model outcomes.",
    "Perturbation-based methodsOne common approach to generating CF is the perturbation-based method.",
    "A perturbation-based method is used in various fields, including machine learning and optimization, to analyze the behavior of a system by modifying input features and keeping the remaining features fixed to observe changes in the prediction."
  ]
}